description:
///
click/tap and drag to navigate
mouse wheel/pinch to zoom
///
A continuation of the piece Infinite Browse, but with hexagon panes.

"The universe (which others call the Library) is composed of an indefinite, perhaps infinite number of hexagonal galleries."
- Jorge Luis Borges

They say that the hexagon is nature's best shape. It definitely solves the circle packing problem. Bees were on it before we even realized it. But it doesn't fit on our screen nicely. It's taller than it is wide (not a square).
///
made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao)
///
